						               													<description>Plant. Grow. Harvest. Sell. Farmers Market is a game themed around supplying customers with what they desire at the local farmers market. During the game, players will plant corn, wheat grain, potatoes seeds, wait for them to grow so they can harvest them. Milk can be drawn from Cows, and the rare chicken can also be found annoying the players if they don't supply a customer who needs a chicken/ cow their eggs/milk. After the goods are ready, they can be transported to the River Street Farmers Market for consumption.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Other options in the game include advancing the technology to get a greater harvest, planting long-growing watermelons (the hit of the day).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Deck manipulation is the main mechanism in farmers market. Players each have their own deck of staple cards. Unlike a normal deck builder, during the game, a few cards will be added to their deck (plant) that will be removed next time they are drawn. Other cards may be added to your deck to help out the harvesting of crops, or change cows or chickens to milk, eggs, or meat, if the patrons request it.&amp;#10;On a player's turn,  they draw and play all 5 cards,  keeping one card from turn to turn if storing it. &amp;#10;The game ends when all the patrons have showed up and asked for their wants.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;A solo game exists that has a timer of rounds, in the way of patron cards orders that must filled before you run out of time.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The patron cards pages must be printed 3 times. &amp;#10;The farmers market 10 pages of cards need to be printed once per player. The backside picture may be printed on the back of the harvest cards,  not the patron cards.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
